%U A394948 96945798218,406374018190,1708703544735,7205047314279,30460421550929,129084872786579,548247473584071
%N A394948 Number of equivalence classes of well-formed bracketed words of total length 2n built from the symbol * (of length 2) and two unary bracket types () and [], with no empty bracket pair, modulo commutativity of concatenation.
%C A394948 a(0)=1 counts the empty word.
%C A394948 For n>=1, a(n)=b_{2,2}^m(2n) in the notation of Au and Bremner; see Section 4.1.
%C A394948 Here two bracketed words are equivalent if they differ only by permuting factors in any concatenation.
%C A394948 The two unary bracket types are distinguished and do not commute under nesting.
%C A394948 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted unordered trees with n vertices in which each leaf represents *, each unary internal node is labeled 1 or 2, and every non-unary internal node has at least 2 unordered children.
%H A394948 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026. See pp. 4, 28 (Table 7).
%F A394948 G.f.: 1 + A(x) = exp(Sum_{k>=1} (x^k + 2*x^k*A(x^k))/k).
%F A394948 n*a(n) = c(n) + Sum_{k=1..n-1} c(k)*a(n-k) for n>1, with a(0)=a(1)=1, where c(n) = Sum_{m|n} m*b(m), b(1)=1, and b(n)=2*a(n-1) for n>=2.
%e A394948 a(3)=9. Representatives for the 9 equivalence classes are ***, (**), [**], (*)*, [*]*, ((*)), ([*]), [(*)], [[*]].
%Y A394948 Cf. A000081, A394949, A394950, A001003.
